#compdef tlm
# =============================================================================
# tlm — Yusuf Can Bayrak's "Local CLI Copilot, powered by Ollama"
#       — a Go command-line LLM copilot that uses LOCALLY-RUNNING
#       Ollama models (qwen2.5-coder, llama3.2, etc.) for command
#       suggestion + explanation + Q&A over local file contexts.
#       Distinguishing from GitHub Copilot CLI, Aider, llm (Simon
#       Willison's), Mods (Charm), and other AI CLI tools by:
#         - LOCAL-FIRST via Ollama — NO API keys, NO data leaves
#           your machine; uses jmorganca/ollama (Ollama Go client)
#           to talk to a locally-running Ollama daemon
#         - 4 SUBCOMMANDS:
#             - tlm suggest "<prompt>" — generate shell command
#             - tlm explain "<command>" — explain shell command
#             - tlm ask "<prompt>" — Q&A over local file context
#             - tlm config — manage tlm configuration
#         - GLOB-INCLUDE/EXCLUDE for ASK context — `tlm ask
#           --context . --include "*.md" --exclude "**/*_test.go"
#           "<prompt>"` packs matching files into the LLM's
#           context window via doublestar glob matching
#         - 3 GENERATION STYLES via --style stable|balanced|creative
#           — sets temperature + sampling parameters for
#           deterministic vs varied outputs
#         - PER-COMMAND MODEL OVERRIDE via --model — try different
#           Ollama models per invocation without changing config
#         - RAG-STYLE CONTEXT PACKING via internal `packer`
#           module — walks --context directory with doublestar
#           globs, sorts files by token count, packs top-N files
#           into the LLM context with a summary header
#         - INTERACTIVE CHAT MODE via --interactive / -it on ask
#           subcommand — multi-turn conversation with persistent
#           context
#         - RELEASE-MANAGER built-in — `releaseManager` metadata
#           handles self-update prompts when newer GitHub releases
#           are available
#       Used by: developers wanting AI command-line assistance
#       without sending data to OpenAI/Anthropic/etc., privacy-
#       conscious teams running local Ollama deployments, and as
#       a reference implementation of doublestar + urfave/cli +
#       Ollama Go client integration.
#
# Author:  Yusuf Can Bayrak (yusufcanb on GitHub) — Turkish Go +
#          AI developer.  tlm released 2024; active development
#          through 2026 with regular releases.  License: MIT.
# Source:  https://github.com/yusufcanb/tlm
#          https://github.com/yusufcanb/tlm/blob/main/pkg/app/app.go
#          https://github.com/yusufcanb/tlm/blob/main/pkg/ask/cli.go
#          https://github.com/yusufcanb/tlm/blob/main/pkg/packer/ (doublestar usage)
# CLI:     pkg/app/app.go — uses urfave/cli/v2 with 4 subcommands +
#          per-subcommand StringFlag/StringSliceFlag/BoolFlag/
#          PathFlag definitions.  Headline library:
#          **bmatcuk/doublestar** (urfave/cli is well-documented;
#          doublestar is the new variant being documented here,
#          expanding Axis 14 to 2 Go variants).
# Library: github.com/bmatcuk/doublestar
#          ("doublestar" — Bob Matcuk (bmatcuk on GitHub) —
#           released 2014 as "Implements support for double star
#           (**) matches in golang's path.Match and filepath.Glob".
#           Distinct from afero (R638, the Go Axis 14 opener) by
#           being:
#             1. ** RECURSIVE GLOB SUPPORT — Go's stdlib
#                path/filepath.Match() supports `*`, `?`, `[abc]`
#                but NOT `**` (zero-or-more path segments).
#                doublestar adds `**` support that matches
#                arbitrary path segments:
#                  doublestar.Match("**/*.go", "src/foo/bar/baz.go") → true
#                  filepath.Match("**/*.go", "src/foo/bar/baz.go") → false
#                  // (stdlib doesn't understand **)
#             2. EXTGLOB SUPPORT — doublestar/v4+ supports the
#                full bash extended glob dialect:
#                  ?(pattern)  — zero or one
#                  *(pattern)  — zero or more
#                  +(pattern)  — one or more
#                  @(pattern)  — exactly one
#                  !(pattern)  — negation
#                  {a,b,c}     — alternation
#                  [a-z]       — character class
#                Matching the full bash extglob + brace-expansion
#                + character-class semantics on filesystem paths
#             3. FOUR API MODES (in doublestar/v4):
#                  doublestar.Match(pattern, name)  // pattern match only
#                  doublestar.Glob(fsys, pattern)   // filesystem walk
#                  doublestar.GlobWalk(fsys, pat, fn) // streaming
#                  doublestar.PathMatch(pat, name)   // OS-specific paths
#             4. fs.FS COMPATIBLE (v4+) — doublestar/v4 uses Go
#                1.16's io/fs.FS interface, making it compose
#                naturally with afero (R638), embed.FS, testing/
#                fstest.MapFS, S3-backed fs implementations,
#                etc.
#             5. MULTI-PATH-SEPARATOR HANDLING — correctly
#                handles Windows backslash + Unix forward-slash
#                + mixed separators in patterns
#             6. ESCAPE-CHARACTER SUPPORT — backslash-escaped
#                literal characters work in patterns + paths
#                (matching POSIX glob behavior)
#             7. HEAVY DOWNSTREAM USAGE — used by hashicorp/
#                copywrite (R607 already documented), snyk/
#                driftctl, ZupIT/horusec, mutagen-io/mutagen
#                (4k stars), camptocamp/terraboard (2k stars),
#                yusufcanb/tlm (THIS), and 1500+ Go applications
#                needing ** glob support for config-file
#                matching + dependency-graph file matching +
#                test-fixture discovery)
# License: MIT (tlm); MIT (doublestar)
# Status:  tlm — 1,484+ stars on yusufcanb/tlm, growing user base
